Citation.sAbstract: The physical property data (densities, excess molar volumes, viscosities, surface tensions, and refractive  indices) for ethanol + glycerol have been determined at 294 K and atmospheric pressure. Densities were  determined by a vibrating-tube densitometer, viscosities were determined by U-tube viscometers, surface  tensions were determined by the Du Nouy ring method, and refractive indices were determined by an Abbe  refractometer. Excess molar volumes were computed from density values and were fit to the Redlich-Kister  equation.
Citation.sTitle: Physical Properties (Density, Excess Molar Volume, Viscosity, Surface Tension, and Refractive Index) of Ethanol + Glycerol
